HEADWORD: Nephridium
<hw>Ne*phrid"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Nephridia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ of the <ets>kidneys</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool. & Anat.)</fld>
<def>A segmental tubule; one of the tubules of the primitive
urinogenital organs; a segmental organ. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Loeven's larva</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

